statement:
Let

\begin{align*}\alpha = \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 \\ 2 & 3 & 4 & 1 \end{pmatrix}\end{align*}
and

\begin{align*}\beta = \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 \\ 2 & 1 & 3 & 4 \end{pmatrix}\end{align*}
be two permutations of \{1, 2, 3, 4\}. Find the composition
$\alpha \circ \beta$.

sols:
Since the composition $\alpha \circ \beta$ is given by doing $\beta$
first and then $\alpha$, we must have that

\begin{align*}
1 \mapsto 2 \mapsto 3 \\
2 \mapsto 1 \mapsto 2 \\
3 \mapsto 3 \mapsto 4 \\
4 \mapsto 4 \mapsto 1\end{align*}

and so we have that $\alpha \circ \beta$ is given by

\begin{align*}\alpha \circ \beta = \begin{pmatrix}1 & 2 & 3 & 4 \\ 3 & 2 & 4 & 1 \end{pmatrix}\end{align*}
